-- Mexico on Hurricane Watch as Depression Three-E Forms
-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 2012-06-14T04:41:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/mexico-on-hurricane-watch-as-depression-three-e-forms-1-.html
A tropical depression formed in the
 Pacific Ocean , prompting Mexico to issue a hurricane warning for
the southern coast of the country, the National Hurricane Center
said in an advisory.  The system, named Three-E, formed about 515 miles (830
kilometers) south east of Puerto Angel, Mexico, and is expected
to strengthen, according to the advisory at 8 p.m. Pacific time
yesterday. The wind speed is 35 miles per hour.  The cyclone is expected to approach the southern coast of
Mexico tomorrow, the enter said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
